The eagle’s beak rests just one-eighth of an inch
above the cup in Ganymede’s hand

The
cup Ganymede holds in his left hand is modeled after a kylix

The eagle was sculpted with such zoological
exactness—from the lifelike layering of feathers to the curved tips of its talons

Thorvaldsen focuses on Ganymede’s interior experience
rather than any exterior reaction.

Ganymede wears is a Phrygian cap, also known as
a liberty cap
